<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>He is a successful Hollywood actor with a film career spanning four decades.</p>

<p>And Matt Dillon cut a dapper figure as he attended the closing ceremony of the Venice Film Festival with his girlfriend Roberta Mastromichele on Saturday.</p>

<p>The actor, 56, donned a black tuxedo along with a crisp white shirt and a black bow tie as he walked the red carpet with his other half, 44.</p>

<p>Couple: Matt Dillon, 56, cut a dapper figure as he attended the closing ceremony of the Venice Film Festival with his girlfriend Roberta Mastromichele, 44, on Saturday</p>

<p>Roberta looked sensational in a white sleeveless dress with an embroidered detail and a plunging neckline.</p>

<p>The garment also featured a floral detail and a ruffled embellishment at the hemline while Roberta let her locks fall loose down her shoulders. </p>

<p>Matt was also joined at the event by Cate Blanchett who he posed alongside on the red carpet.  </p>

<p>The Venice Film Festival is one of the world's oldest award ceremonies and is listed as one of the 'Big Five' events. It started on Wednesday and ends on the 12 September. </p>

<p>Event: The actor donned a black tuxedo along with a crisp white shirt and a black bow tie as he walked the red carpet with his other half </p>

<p>Stars: Matt was also joined at the event by Cate Blanchett who he posed alongside on the red carpet </p>

<p>History: The Venice Film Festival is one of the world's oldest award ceremonies and is listed as one of the 'Big Five' events </p>

<p>Changes: Though the event is still taking place, it is a markedly toned down affair to previous years amid the coronavirus crisis </p>

<p>Though the event is still taking place, it is a markedly toned down affair to previous years amid the coronavirus crisis, with temperature checks and mask wearing becoming mandatory. </p>

<p>Matt joined writer-director Veronika Franz, UK writer-director Joanna Hogg, writer Nicola Lagioia, German filmmaker Christian Petzol and French star Lucivine Sagnier on the Festival's main competition jury, which is presided over by actress Cate Blanchett. </p>

<p>The actor rose to prominence in the late '80s with roles in films such as the Outsiders and Rumble Fix.</p>

<p>In 2006, he received Golden Globe and Oscar nominations for his critically-acclaimed role in Crash opposite Sandra Bullock.</p>

<p>Since then, he has gone on to star in dozens of films including the gruesome flick The House That Jack built in 2018.</p>

